The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at the Inglesia de Dios church in Orlando, Florida, expressing support for the Puerto Rico and U.S. Virgin Islands communities in the wake of Hurricane Maria. He thanked the state of Florida for their response to Hurricane Irma and their generosity towards Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands. Pence also mentioned that he and his wife will be traveling to Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands to lend a hand and deliver the message that the administration stands with them. He highlighted the efforts of federal officials, FEMA, and the Armed Forces in providing aid and support to the affected areas. Pence assured that progress is being made in terms of restoring services and infrastructure, but emphasized the need for continued assistance from the American people. He concluded by expressing confidence in the leadership of President Trump and the dedication of local and federal officials, and stated that Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands will rebuild and thrive once again.